               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1603" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1603" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1603" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1603" type="given" value="ROBERT SAMUEL"></interp>ROBERT SAMUEL PEARSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a rafter in the Commercial Dock, and live with my mother, in Russell-street, Rotherhithe. The prisoner came to lodge there on the evening of the 2nd of March—he slept with me that night—I got up at half-past six o'clock next morning, and went to work, leaving him in bed—I did not miss my clothes till that evening, when I went to put them on—they had been hanging up in the room where we slept—these are my jacket, trowsers, and shoes—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1604" type="witnessName">
